The World Energy Balances data contains energy balances for 156      countries and expressed in kilo tonnes of oil equivalent (ktoe).      Conversion factors used to calculate energy balances and      indicators (including GDP, population, industrial production index      and ratios calculated with the energy data) are also provided. The      database also includes transparent notes on methodologies and      sources for country-level data. In general, the data are available      from 1971 (1960 for OECD countries) to 2022. Preliminary 2023 data      are available for select countries, products, and flows.
